<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak direction-ltr" data-module="govspeak">
      <div class="govspeak">
<div class="call-to-action">
<h2 id="stay-up-to-date">Stay up to date</h2>

<p>The UK is leaving the EU. This page tells you how to prepare for Brexit and will be updated if anything changes.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/email-signup?topic=%2Fbrexit">Sign up for email alerts</a> to get the latest information.</p>
</div>

<ol class="steps">
<li>
<p>Ask your higher education provider how Brexit will affect you, including what tuition fees you’ll have to pay.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Check what your residency and healthcare rights will be by using the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/overseas-living-in-guides">living in country guides</a>.</p>
</li>
</ol>

<h2 id="completing-your-studies-in-the-uk">Completing your studies in the UK</h2>

<p>You’ll need to check:</p>

<ul>
  <li>with <a rel="external" href="https://www.ucas.com/brexit">UCAS</a> what courses will be available to you in the UK</li>
  <li>whether you can <a rel="external" href="https://www.officeforstudents.org.uk/for-students/brexit-advice-for-students/uk-nationals-studying-in-the-eu/transferring-to-a-uk-higher-education-provider/">transfer to a UK higher education provider</a> after Brexit</li>
  <li>with your preferred provider whether you’ll have to wait until the next academic year to start your course</li>
</ul>

<p>Before you return to the UK, obtain evidence relating to your studies, like transcripts of study or certification of unit modules.</p>

<h2 id="check-whether-youll-get-financial-help">Check whether you’ll get financial help</h2>

<p>Ask the student finance body of the country you were studying in before you left the UK whether you’re eligible for funding to complete your studies in the UK.</p>

<p>If you’ve never lived in the UK, contact the student finance body for the country you want to study in.</p>

<ul>
  <li><a href="https://www.gov.uk/student-finance">Student Finance England</a></li>
  <li><a rel="external" href="https://www.saas.gov.uk/">Student Awards Agency Scotland</a></li>
  <li><a rel="external" href="https://www.studentfinancewales.co.uk/">Student Finance Wales</a></li>
  <li><a rel="external" href="https://www.studentfinanceni.co.uk/">Student Finance Northern Ireland</a></li>
</ul>

<p>If you wish to apply for student finance, your student funding body may ask you to provide evidence to show you had to come back to the UK, like a letter from your current higher education provider.</p>

<h2 id="erasmus-students-already-studying-in-the-eu">Erasmus+ students already studying in the EU</h2>

<p>You should still be able to continue with your placement when Brexit happens.</p>

<p>Read the guidance on <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/student-finance-arrangements-in-a-no-deal-scenario">student finance after Brexit</a> for more details.</p>

</div>
</div>


